Date: 2001-01-18

Title: Noncommutative Solitons and Intersecting D-Branes

Authors: Li-Sheng Tseng

Comments: 17 pages, harvmac; published version with added clarifications

Journal-ref: Phys.Rev. D64 (2001) 126004

We construct intersecting D-branes as noncommutative solitons in bosonic andtype II string theory. ``Defect'' branes which are D-branes containing bubblesof the closed string vacuum play an important role in the construction.